function Start(idActorKiller, idActorKilled)
	local portalCount = Hydra.ActorsInPrefabScopedGroup("US_Demon_Invasion_Portal")
	
	-- Takes a second for the portal to actually be cleared from the group. So if there's only one left at this time, it's the one being cleaned up
	if #portalCount > 1 then
		return
	end
	
	-- If we've already completed this quest step we don't want to spawn more portals.
	local nPortalsKilled = Hydra.QuestCallbackCountGet(172)
	if nPortalsKilled >= 7 then
		return
	end
	
	if B_IS_DEMONWAVE == true then
		S_MonsterFamily = "FAMILY_DEMON"
		
		SpawnPortal(ptCenter, S_DEMON_PORTAL_LARGE)	
	else
		S_MonsterFamily = "FAMILY_MAIN"
		
		for i = 1, N_PORTALS do
			SpawnPortal(getBestSpawn(Hydra.ActorsInPrefabScopedGroup("US_Demon_Invasion_Portal"), N_PORTAL_DIST_MIN, N_PORTAL_DIST_MAX), S_DEMON_PORTAL)
		end
		
		B_IS_DEMONWAVE = true
	end
end

-- Check to see if a point we want to spawn is to close to another
local function isNearPortal(pt, tPortalsToCheck)	
	local ptToCheck
	
	local flDistance = 0
	
	for i = 1, #tPortalsToCheck do
		ptToCheck = Hydra.ActorGetPosition(tPortalsToCheck[i])
		flDistance = Hydra.PositionGetDistanceToPosition(pt, ptToCheck)
		
		if flDistance < N_PORTAL_DIST_MIN then
			return true, flDistance
		end		
	end
	
	return false
end

-- Find the best spawn location for a new portal
local function getBestSpawn(tAvoidLocations, nMinDistance, nMaxDistance)	
	local flBestDist = 0
	local ptBest
	
	if #tAvoidLocations == 0 then
		return Hydra.PositionSearchForNearbyNavmeshPosition(ptCenter, nMinDistance, nMaxDistance)
	else
		for i = 1, 30 do
			local ptSpawn = Hydra.PositionSearchForNearbyNavmeshPosition(ptCenter, nMinDistance, nMaxDistance)
			
			local bIsNear, flDistCheck = isNearPortal(ptSpawn, tAvoidLocations)
			
			if not bIsNear then
				ptSpawn = Hydra.PositionSnapToGround(ptSpawn)
				return ptSpawn
			else
				if flDistCheck > flBestDist then
					flBestDist = flDistCheck
					ptBest = ptSpawn
				end
			end	
		end
	
		Hydra.PositionSnapToGround(ptBest)
		return ptBest
	end
	

end


local function SpawnPortal(ptSpawn, s_portal_to_spawn)
	local pfDefault = Hydra.FacingFromYaw(0)
	local aPortal = Hydra.ActorSpawnActor(s_portal_to_spawn, ptSpawn, pfDefault, true, 0, 0)

	Hydra.ActorAddToPrefabScopedGroup(aPortal, "US_Demon_Invasion_Portal")

	Hydra.BuffApplyToTarget(S_PORTAL_POWER, S_MonsterFamily, aPortal)
	
	Hydra.ActorMergeAIState(aPortal, S_PORTAL_AI, aPortal, 0)
	
	-- If it's a demon wave, spawn a bonus elite demon for each portal
	if B_IS_DEMONWAVE == true then
		B_IS_DEMONWAVE = false
		
		-- Make sure this isn't the initial portal. We don't want any elites spawning as part of the first portal
		if N_PORTALS < 4 and N_PORTALS > 1 then
			N_PORTALS = N_PORTALS + 1
			
			for i = 2, N_PORTALS do
	
				local sMonster = Hydra.ActorPickFromEncounter(S_DEMON_ELITES, aPortal)
				Hydra.Wait(1.5)
				
				-- Make sure the portal is still alive when we want to spawn the elite
				if Hydra.ActorIsValid(aPortal) then
					local aMonster = Hydra.ActorSpawnActor(sMonster, ptSpawn, pfDefault, true, 0.5, 1.5, 1)
					Hydra.ActorAddToPrefabScopedGroup(aMonster, "US_Demon_Invasion_Mobs")
					local ptFX = Hydra.ActorGetPosition(aMonster)
					Hydra.ActorPlayEffectGroupActorToActor(aPortal, aMonster, S_SUMMON_EFFECTS)
					Hydra.ActorPlayEffectGroup(aMonster, S_SUMMON_EFFECTS_TARGET)
				else
					break
				end
			end
		else
			N_PORTALS = 2
		end
		

	end
end
